          <declname>dest</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const char *</type>
          <declname>src</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="group___standard_memory_1ga7c94ea6f8948649f8d181ae55911eeaf" kindref="member">size_t</ref></type>
          <declname>n</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Copies up to n bytes from the string in src into dest and null terminates dest. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>If dest is null terminated before n bytes have been written, null bytes will continue to be written until n bytes total were written. There should be no overlap of dest and src in memory. <parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>dest</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The destination buffer with enough space for n bytes </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>src</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The source string </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>n</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The number of bytes to copy </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>The destination buffer dest </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
